HEADWORD: cryptanalysis
<hw>crypt"a*nal"y*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>the science which studies methods to discovering the secret meaning
of encrypted messages for which one does not possess the secret decoding
information (called the <er>key</er>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the methods and procedures used to discover the
secret meaning hidden in encrypted messages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cryptical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Cryptic</ent>⟦br⟧
